# Linux on Leros
A future goal for the Leros processor is to be able to boot an operating system, such as a tiny Linux distro.
A distribution build system should be utilized, such as Yocto or BuildRoot.

*Resources:*
* https://wiki.yoctoproject.org/wiki/Poky-Tiny
  * Starting point for a tiny linux distro, based on BusyBox
* https://elinux.org/images/0/0a/Creating-Your-Own-Tiny-Linux-Distribution-Using-Yocto-Keeping-it-Small-With-Poky-Tiny-Alejandro-Hernandez-Xilinx.pdf
